author: maxb
msg: A collection of work on "type **" parameters in the SWIG bindings.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* core.i, svn_client.i, svn_delta.i, svn_fs.i, svn_ra.i, svn_repos.i, svn_wc.i:
Move the '%apply SWIGTYPE **OUTPARAM' clauses...
* include/svn_types.swg: ...to here, and clean them up, removing duplicates
and instances of 'void **' (too general, might do something unexpected),
adding named 'void **some_name' entries, and some additional types.
Add general "type **" typemaps, including collapsing the "in" typemap to a
single language-neutral one. This involved deleting an instance of
"temp = NULL;" from the Ruby bindings - I think this is OK, because if the
other languages are not using it, I cannot see why Ruby should need it.
* include/apr.swg: Remove some 'apr_hash_t **' typemaps which are replaced by
the generic "type **" code.

author: rooneg
